New Records: Trae Young scored 24 points and recorded 20 assists, setting a new career high for assists in a single game.
Lauri Markkanen matched his season high with 35 points.
Key Match Events: Trae Young made a game-winning half-court shot as time expired.
Collin Sexton tied the game with a three-pointer with four seconds left.
Walker Kessler scored 10 straight points in the fourth quarter to keep the Jazz in the game.
Post-Match Reflections: The Atlanta Hawks ended their three-game losing streak with the win.
The Utah Jazz fell to 2-13 at home on the season.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was played at the Delta Center in Salt Lake City.
The Atlanta Hawks played without their second-leading scorer Jalen Johnson due to injury.
